---
import { Icon } from 'astro-icon/components';
import SectionTitle from '@/components/sections/common/SectionTitle.astro';
import Button from '@/components/ui/Button.astro';
---

<section class="relative mx-auto mt-32 mb-32 max-w-7xl px-4">
  <div class="mb-8 text-center">
    <SectionTitle>Benchmarks</SectionTitle>
    <h2 class="mb-6 text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white md:text-5xl">
      <span class="text-primary">AtlasOS</span> vs. <span class="text-white/70">Stock Windows</span>
    </h2>
    <p class="mx-auto max-w-2xl leading-relaxed text-white/70">
      With reduced resource utilization, improved privacy, usability, and performance, why wouldn't you consider making
      the switch?
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-12 text-center">
    <Button
      href="https://github.com/orgs/Atlas-OS/discussions/1161"
      icon="tabler:arrow-up-right"
      iconPosition="after"
      external
      variant="primary"
      size="lg"
    >
      View detailed benchmark
    </Button>
  </div>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-16 md:grid-cols-3 md:gap-20">
    <div class="relative py-2">
      <div class="flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-white/5">
        <Icon name="tabler:cpu" class="h-6 w-6 text-white/80" />
      </div>
      <h3 class="mt-5 mb-3 text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white">CPU usage</h3>
      <p class="leading-relaxed text-white/70">
        We've reduced background CPU spikes significantly. Nothing that you don't need will run in the background.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-4 flex items-baseline gap-2">
        <span class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white/70">2â€‘10%</span>
        <Icon name="tabler:arrow-narrow-right" class="h-5 w-5 text-white/70" aria-hidden="true" />
        <span class="text-primary text-2xl font-semibold">0%</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="relative py-2">
      <div class="flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-white/5">
        <Icon name="tabler:database" class="h-6 w-6 text-white/80" />
      </div>
      <h3 class="mt-5 mb-3 text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white">RAM usage</h3>
      <p class="leading-relaxed text-white/70">
        Thanks to Atlas we've seen ~1.5 GB of RAM usage freed on boot, which can then be allocated to other tasks.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-4 flex items-baseline gap-2">
        <span class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white/70">2.9 GB</span>
        <Icon name="tabler:arrow-narrow-right" class="h-5 w-5 text-white/70" aria-hidden="true" />
        <span class="text-primary text-2xl font-semibold">~1.4 GB</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="relative py-2">
      <div class="flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-white/5">
        <Icon name="tabler:gauge" class="h-6 w-6 text-white/80" />
      </div>
      <h3 class="mt-5 mb-3 text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white">Higher FPS in games</h3>
      <p class="leading-relaxed text-white/70">
        Higher average framerates observed in competitive titles like Valorant on Windows 11.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-white/50">Ryzen 7 5800X3D, 16GB 3600MHz, RTX 2070 Super</p>
      <div class="mt-4 flex items-baseline gap-2">
        <span class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white/70">217.5 FPS</span>
        <Icon name="tabler:arrow-narrow-right" class="h-5 w-5 text-white/70" aria-hidden="true" />
        <span class="text-primary text-2xl font-semibold">365.91 FPS</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
